# Robowarz 2.0
Prepare to experience the ultimate showdown in our thrilling competition – Robowars 2.0! With random groupings and challenging league matches, only the best bots will advance to the higher rounds.

The top teams will go head-to-head in a 5-minute battle to claim the ultimate victory. Are you ready to take on the challenge and emerge as the champion? Then sign up now for the Robowars 2.0!

---
## Rules & Regulations
Robot Specification:
1. Permissible weight: Maximum 60 kg (excluding off-bot power equipment e.g. batteries, adapters
etc.)
2. Permissible Size: Fully unfolded robot must be within the limits of 40 cm X 55 cm (l x b).
3. Use of liquid projectiles, any kind of inflammable liquid, flame-based weapons, radio jamming
devices, high power magnets or electromagnets, are not permitted.
4. Participating teams need to bring their own adapters/converters (with a maximum output voltage
of 36 V DC) to avail AC supply.
5. In case of batteries, maximum allowed voltage is 36 V DC.

### General Rules:
1. Each team can have maximum five members.
2. Robots will be inspected for safety and reliability before being allowed to compete.
3. Disrupting opponent’s power is not allowed.
4. Organizers reserve the right to ban/disqualify any robot at any point of time, due to safety or any
other reason.

### Game Rules:
1. The competition will be played on a knock-out basis consisting of 2 players at a time.
2. The maximum duration of each War/Fight will be 5 minutes.
3. The robot will win if the robot pushes the opponent to the ditch successfully or successfully
immobilizes the opponent.
4. Match will be interrupted if crossings of wire will take place.
5. No member will be allowed to enter in the war zone without permission of coordinators.
6. The organizers reserve the rights to change any or all of the above rules as they deem fit.
7. Violation of any the above rules will lead to disqualification.
8. Judges' decision shall be treated as final and binding on all.


### Prize money 
1st place 30,000 rupees
2nd place  20,000 rupees
 
Time - 10 am to 4 pm

